==English==

===Proper Noun===
'''Maxwell'''
# a [[Scottish]] [[habitational]] [[surname]] from ''Maccuswell,'' or ''Maxwell,'' a minor town on the [[Wikipedia:River Tweed|River Tweed]] near [[Wikipedia:Kelso|Kelso]], to where the family had migrated from England about 1100. The town's name means "the stream [Old English ''well(a)''] of Mack [a form of ''Magnus'']".
# A male [[given name]] derived from the surname

